				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twisting Songs<a name="74583"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 17 05 4:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Personally for me when doing manual twisting ... (which is almost all i do).. if you were to take the spell gems one through nine they conicide with the number pad on the right of the right of the keyboard. 
<br />

<br />
I can rest my fingers across them and just double tap what ever song it is I want. I then move with my left hand on the arrow keys.
<br />

<br />
Though I do use third person view most of the time during the course of the song cast i will move my hand to the mouse to move camera..
<br />

<br />
Works for me.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Keyboard (number area)
<br />

<br />
% / * -
<br />
7 8 9 +
<br />
4 5 6
<br />
1 2 3 $
<br />
0 
<br />

<br />
-= cycle through mobs
<br />
7= gem 1
<br />
8= gem 2
<br />
9= gem 3
<br />
+= gem 4 (Big key easy to hit Mana Regen song.)
<br />
4= gem 5
<br />
5= gem 6
<br />
6= gem 7
<br />
*= gem 8 ($ represents enter key on number pad)
<br />
0= auto twist
<br />
3=gem 9
<br />
1= changes camera view
<br />

<br />
For me this allows me to hit any of my nine songs quickly with out looking or moving a mouse. It also allows me to change camera view to see if pathers or if i have one mezzed that I am not bouncing him to far out. And to cycle through multiple mobs quikcly..
<br />

<br />
Also lets me keep my hotkey bank open. Thinking about adding fade to the number pad as well. Number 2 still open....</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
