				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twisting Songs<a name="74588"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 17 05 8:41 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have the row of numbers hooked up to my hotkeys...1-7 are songs, 8 is bellow, 9 is songblade, and 0 is fade.
<br />

<br />
I can play for hours with leaving my fingers on 1,2,3,4 using 'e' to target nearest npc and q to cycle npc's, ~ for autoattack, and caps lock for toggling between 2 targets
<br />

<br />
And arrows for movement...
<br />

<br />
This way I never have to touch the mouse unless I'm changing spells or equipment...I played so often with my hands never moving that my laptop has wear marks beneath the left Ctrl and Alt, and beneath the arrow keys...its quite sad really =p
<br />

<br />
But to each his own...I personally like the responsivness of the keyboard...</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
